# Tornado Core Project Structure

This is a privacy-focused cryptocurrency mixing protocol built with zero-knowledge proofs. The project structure is organized as follows:

## Core Components

- **Circuits** (`circuits/`): Zero-knowledge proof circuits written in Circom
  - [merkleTree.circom](mdc:circuits/merkleTree.circom) - Merkle tree implementation for privacy
  - [withdraw.circom](mdc:circuits/withdraw.circom) - Withdrawal proof circuit

- **Smart Contracts** (`contracts/`): Solidity contracts for the protocol
  - [Tornado.sol](mdc:contracts/Tornado.sol) - Main tornado contract
  - [ETHTornado.sol](mdc:contracts/ETHTornado.sol) - ETH-specific tornado implementation
  - [ERC20Tornado.sol](mdc:contracts/ERC20Tornado.sol) - ERC20 token tornado implementation
  - [MerkleTreeWithHistory.sol](mdc:contracts/MerkleTreeWithHistory.sol) - On-chain merkle tree

- **Source Code** (`src/`): JavaScript utilities and CLI
  - [cli.js](mdc:src/cli.js) - Command-line interface
  - [config.js](mdc:src/config.js) - Configuration settings
  - [minimal-demo.js](mdc:src/minimal-demo.js) - Demo implementation

- **Deployment** (`migrations/`, `scripts/`): Deployment and build scripts
  - [deploy.js](mdc:deploy.js) - Main deployment script
  - [truffle-config.js](mdc:truffle-config.js) - Truffle configuration

## Key Concepts

This project implements a non-custodial anonymous transaction protocol using:
- Zero-knowledge proofs for privacy
- Merkle trees for efficient proof verification
- Smart contracts for trustless operation
- Support for both ETH and ERC20 tokens
